◆ SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_Anonymous

const S2OPC_COMMON_EXPORT OpcUa_UserTokenPolicy SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_Anonymous

Example of anonymous user security policy supported configuration

◆ SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_UserName_NoneSecurityPolicy

const S2OPC_COMMON_EXPORT OpcUa_UserTokenPolicy SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_UserName_NoneSecurityPolicy

Example username security policy supported and configured with security policy None. With this security policy, the password will never be encrypted and this policy shall not be used on unsecured and unencrypted secure channels.

◆ SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_UserName_DefaultSecurityPolicy

const S2OPC_COMMON_EXPORT OpcUa_UserTokenPolicy SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_UserName_DefaultSecurityPolicy

Example username security policy supported and configured with empty security policy. With this security policy, the password will be encrypted if Secure Channel security policy is not None. It shall not be used on secure channels using security policy None otherwise no encryption will be done.

◆ SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_UserName_Basic256Sha256SecurityPolicy

const S2OPC_COMMON_EXPORT OpcUa_UserTokenPolicy SOPC_UserTokenPolicy_UserName_Basic256Sha256SecurityPolicy

Example username security policy supported and configured with Basic256Sha256 security policy. With this security policy, the password will be encrypted in any SecureChannel security policy and mode.
